'''The Fleece Inn''' is a [[public house]] in [[Bretforton]], [[Worcestershire]] in the [[Vale of Evesham]]: the half-timbered building, over six hundred years old, has been a pub since 1848, and is now owned by the [[National Trust for Places of Historic Interest or Natural Beauty|National Trust]]. The inn was extensively damaged by fire on 27 February 2004 &mdash; repairs and rebuilding commenced on 1 November 2004. The Fleece officially reopened â with a new roof and improved facilities &mdash; on 18 June 2005.<ref>[http://www.nationaltrust.org.uk/main/w-vh/w-visits/w-findaplace/w-thefleeceinn.htm National Trust: The Fleece Inn] Retrieved 9 February 2010</ref>
